      "key": {
        "uuid": "d4f7c01b_ccdf6416",
        "filename": "protocol/restconf-openapi/src/main/java/org/opendaylight/restconf/openapi/netty/OpenApiResourceProvider.java",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 32,
      "author": {
        "id": 9173
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-14T23:12:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We should keep both components bound to the same PID if both consume org.opendaylight.restconf.nb.rfc8040. What we can avoid is defining the same configuration metadata twice.\n\nOpenApiResourceProvider does not need its own @Designate/Configuration; it can read api-root-path from activation properties instead, leaving OSGiNorthbound.Configuration is the one place defining the config schema for that PID.\n\nAnd we cannot just add NettyEndpoint as a parameter of the constructor, because that introduces a circular dependency: NettyEndpoint depends on WebHostResourceProvider, and OpenApiResourceProvider would then depend back on NettyEndpoint.",
      "parentUuid": "5fbdf053_eb9395a5",
      "revId": "90998978c4adbbda17315e9e293f7d115c60d704",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
    },
